e. In an era of unstable cultural policy and funding, Uplift draws welcome attention to the place of fine arts, culture, and the humanities in public education and in Canada’s history.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aArts and societyzAlbertazBanff National ParkxHistoryy20th century. 0aArtsxStudy and teachingzAlbertazBanff National ParkxHistoryy20th century. 0aArts, CanadianzAlbertazBanff National Parky20th century. 0aTourism and the artszAlbertazBanff National ParkxHistoryy20th century. 7aHISTORY / Canada / Post-Confederation (1867-).2bisacsh1 aWall, Karen, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311127253508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2020z978311127473708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of British Columbia Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311141765340uhttps://doi.org/10.59962/978077486453440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780774864534423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780774864534/original  a978-3-11-127253-5  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-127473-7  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-141765-3  University of British Columbia Complete eBook-Package 2020b2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles